  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Adjudication is the formal process by which a legal body resolves a dispute or determines a question of law. A judge hears arguments, evaluates evidence, applies legal rules, and issues a decision that binds the parties. The decision becomes part of the legal record and, in common law systems, may bind future courts through [precedent](../schools/american-law/terms/legal-precedent.md).",
